   "body" : "I didn't have this with 0.9.1-beta, but now when I gracefully stop (bitcoind stop) bitcoind I get this in console:\n\n`\nbitcoind getinfoterminate called after throwing an instance of 'boost::exception_detail::clone_impl<boost::exception_detail::error_info_injector<boost::system::system_error> >'\n  what():  cancel: Bad file descriptor\n`\nIt doesn't bother me, but it looks ugly and I didn't see this before with 0.9.1-beta.\n\nBefore shutdown service appears to be doing fine (no errors):\n`\n bitcoind getinfo\n{\n    \"version\" : 90200,\n    \"protocolversion\" : 70002,\n    \"blocks\" : 75256,\n    \"timeoffset\" : 0,\n    \"connections\" : 2,\n    \"proxy\" : \"\",\n    \"difficulty\" : 511.77353426,\n    \"testnet\" : false,\n    \"relayfee\" : 0.00001000,\n    \"errors\" : \"\"\n}`\n\nShutdown log seems normal.\n\n`$ tail -f .bitcoin/debug.log`\n`2014-06-16 20:39:49 Shutdown : In progress...`\n`2014-06-16 20:39:49 StopNode()`\n`2014-06-16 20:39:54 Shutdown : done`\n`2014-06-16 20:40:07 117 addresses found from DNS seeds`\n`2014-06-16 20:40:07 dnsseed thread exit`\n`2014-06-16 20:40:07 Shutdown : In progress...`\n\nMy OS: \n`\nuname -a\nLinux raspberry 3.12.19+ #681 PREEMPT Fri May 9 16:36:10 BST 2014 armv6l GNU/Linux\n`\n",
